Any Premier League clubs hoping to lure Jurgen Klopp to England were dealt a blow after Borussia Dortmund reiterated that the club has full faith in their under-pressure manager.

Klopp guided Dortmund to Bundesliga titles in 2011 and 2012 but has struggled this season with 10 defeats from 17 games - leaving the former champions second-bottom in the table going in to the winter break.

Nonetheless, general manager Hans-Joachim Watzke told the Bild paper on Tuesday: 'We are fully convinced of him.'

